In 1930 this country went to a great Depression, which led to all the ideas of the state and Social Security and all other things that happened in Roosevelt's time for the 19 eighties. We had the Reagan Revolution, which led to deregulation. And today, after the global economic crisis, we have a whole new set off duels about how the state should intervene. So ideas change. States and I looked at India and said, Really, there are four kinds off ideas which I really make an impact on India. The first, to my mind, is what I call is the idea that I arrived. These ideas have brought together something which has made it made India happened the way it is today. The second set of ideas, I call it ideas in progress. Those are ideas which have been accepted but not implemented yet. The torture of ideas. I want this idea that we argue about those are the idea where we have, ah fight an ideological battle about how to do things. On the fourth thing, which I believe is most important, is the idea that we need to anticipate, because when you're a developing country in a car in the world where you can see the problems that other countries are hiring, you can actually anticipate what they did and do things very differently. Now. In India's case, I believe there are six ideas which are responsible for where it has come today. The first is really the notion off people in the sixties and seventies, we thought off people as a burden. We thought of people as a liability today, the top off people as an asset. You know, people as human capital and I believe this change in the mindset of looking at people from something as a burden to human capital has been one of the fundamental changes in the Indian mindset. And this change in thing of human capital is linked to the fact that India is going through a demographic dividend as healthcare improves as infant mortality goes down fertility rates start dropping and India is experiencing back. And India is goingto have a lot of young people with the demographic dividend for the next 30 years. And what is unique about this demographic dividend is that India will be the only country in the world to have his demographic dividend.
